      "content": "but i read online that medical grade honey (manuka) is actually used in hospitals for wound care because it's antibacterial. if i just clean it really well first and then use a thick layer of that, couldn't i just bandage it up and wait a day to see if it closes? i'm just worried about the cost of an ER visit and it doesn't look *that* deep once the bleeding slows down a bit.",
